      <body xsi:type="ocl.ecore:StringLiteralExp" stringSymbol="&#xA;"/>
      <body xsi:type="ocl.ecore:StringLiteralExp" stringSymbol="&#x9;&#xA;"/>
      <body xsi:type="mtl:FileBlock" openMode="OverWrite">
        <body xsi:type="ocl.ecore:StringLiteralExp" stringSymbol="&#x9;\documentclass{article}&#xA;&#x9;\usepackage{graphicx} &#xA;&#x9;\usepackage{fontenc}&#xA;&#x9;\usepackage{hyperref}&#xA;&#x9;\usepackage{pdflscape}&#xA;&#x9;\usepackage{array}&#xA;&#x9;\usepackage{adjustbox}&#xA;&#x9;\usepackage{todonotes}&#xA;&#x9;\usepackage{xcolor}&#xA;"/>
        <body xsi:type="ocl.ecore:StringLiteralExp" stringSymbol="&#x9;\usepackage{subcaption}&#xA;&#xA;&#x9;\definecolor{level0}{RGB}{220,220,220}&#xA;&#x9;\definecolor{level1}{RGB}{255,200,200}&#xA;&#x9;\definecolor{level2}{RGB}{255,230,180}&#xA;&#x9;\definecolor{level3}{RGB}{200,255,200}&#xA;&#xA;&#x9;\title{Assurance Case Report "/>
        <body xsi:type="ocl.ecore:PropertyCallExp">
          <eType xsi:type="ecore:EDataType" href="platform:/resource/org.eclipse.emf.ecore/model/Ecore.ecore#//EString"/>
          <source xsi:type="ocl.ecore:VariableExp" name="a" referredVariable="/0/generateElement/a">
            <eType xsi:type="ecore:EClass" href="http://www.osate.org/assure/Assure#//AssuranceCaseResult"/>
          </source>
          <referredProperty xsi:type="ecore:EAttribute" href="http://www.osate.org/assure/Assure#//AssuranceCaseResult/name"/>
        </body>
        <body xsi:type="ocl.ecore:StringLiteralExp" stringSymbol="}&#xA;&#x9;\author{x}&#xA;&#x9;\begin{document}&#xA;&#x9;\maketitle&#xA;&#x9;\section{Introduction}&#xA;&#x9;This assurance-case report presents the results of the &#xA;&#x9;representativity evaluation performed on the different model variants considered for &#xA;&#x9;the simulation need. The document is structured to provide a clear and traceable view of how &#xA;&#x9;each model was assessed. For every model variant, the report lists all associated requirements&#xA;&#x9; and specifies whether each requirement has been successfully satisfied. Based on these &#xA;&#x9;individual outcomes, the report then summarizes the performance of each model using the &#xA;&#x9;representativity factors defined in our framework, expressed both as percentage scores &#xA;&#x9;and corresponding levels on the assessment scale. These elements allow the reader to understand &#xA;&#x9;the strengths and limitations of each variant.&#xA;&#x9; &#xA;&#x9;\section{Model Results}&#xA;    Found "/>
        <body xsi:type="ocl.ecore:OperationCallExp">
          <eType xsi:type="ocl.ecore:PrimitiveType" href="http://www.eclipse.org/ocl/1.1.0/oclstdlib.ecore#/0/Integer"/>
          <source xsi:type="ocl.ecore:PropertyCallExp" eType="/15/OrderedSet(ModelResult)">
            <source xsi:type="ocl.ecore:VariableExp" name="a" referredVariable="/0/generateElement/a">
              <eType xsi:type="ecore:EClass" href="http://www.osate.org/assure/Assure#//AssuranceCaseResult"/>
            </source>
            <referredProperty xsi:type="ecore:EReference" href="http://www.osate.org/assure/Assure#//AssuranceCaseResult/modelResult"/>
          </source>
          <referredOperation xsi:type="ecore:EOperation" href="http://www.eclipse.org/ocl/1.1.0/oclstdlib.ecore#/0/OrderedSet(T)_Class/size"/>
        </body>
        <body xsi:type="ocl.ecore:StringLiteralExp" stringSymbol=" modelResults&#xA;&#x9;&#x9;&#xA;"/>
        <body xsi:type="mtl:ForBlock">
          <body xsi:type="ocl.ecore:StringLiteralExp" stringSymbol="&#x9;&#x9;&#x9;\section{Model Result Details} &#xA;&#x9;&#x9;&#x9;\paragraph{Model Summary}&#xA;&#x9;&#x9;&#x9;Number of claims: "/>
